    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-30T18:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-30T18:55:00-05:00" n="239"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <head>239. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d239fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 684A.86/8–3055. Top Secret;<gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>;
                        Alpha; Limited Distribution. Drafted and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RFH1">Russell</persName>, who signed for
                            <persName>Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-30T18:55:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1955—6:55 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>402. You will see from <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 401<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d239fn2">
                        <ref target="#d238">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note> we consider Egypt key to development Arab cooperation in exploring
                    possibilities progress along lines Secretary’s Aug 26 statement. We recognize
                    complications posed by Gaza flareup. You should however impress upon <gloss
                        target="#t_GOE1">GOE</gloss>: 1) Continuation uneasy border situation can
                    only harm Egypt; 2) If not dealt with along lines suggested by Secretary, it
                    will almost inevitably sooner or later break out into larger warfare.</p>
                <pb facs="0450" n="422" xml:id="pg_422"/>
                <p>At your discretion you may add US anxious help <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1"
                        >Nasser</persName> along lines <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss>
                        325<note n="3" xml:id="d239fn3">
                        <ref target="#d207">Document 207</ref>.</note> but our ability assist
                    necessarily affected by possibility of progress in this matter.</p>
                <p>Dept would appreciate your opinion re any tactics US and/or <gloss
                        target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> can take move <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1"
                        >Nasser</persName> toward initiating Trieste approach to Alpha in early
                    future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
